The Lord is God, with thanks expresse, His mercy is for ever : and

2 So let the Lord’s redeem'd confesse, Redeem'd from their distressors hand.

3 Which guthred were out of the lands From shining Bast, from shady &Vest‚ From where the frozen Pole-starre stands From desert south seas sun-burnt brest.

And tooke a solitary way, Where foot of man did seldom presse, Nor found they city where to stay.
